  "title": "UK English Cookie Fix",
  "description": "Fixes the name of \"Cookie\" in UK English",
  "body": "In the UK, cookies and biscuits are different things. Biscuits are a generic term, and a cookie is a type of biscuit. It's technically not incorrect, but it sounds a bit strange. It'd be like if \"beef\" was called \"meat\" ingame. This resource pack corrects it in UK English and makes it sound more natural and normal.\n\nThat's it.\n\n(this texture pack was made for 1.20.2 but will 99.999999999% work for everything after)",
